Leapfrog
========

1.Installation

  Download and copy to vender/plugins folder.



Example
=======

1. Migration file

  Add 't.users' to Migration file in self.up method.


    class CreateUsers < ActiveRecord::Migration
      def self.up
        create_table :users do |t|
          t.string :name
          t.string :password
          t.string :email

          t.timestamps
          t.users     # add column 'created_by' and 'updated_by'
        end
      end

      def self.down
        drop_table :users
      end
    end


  If you want to add column after created tables.
  Then run script/generate migration add_users_to_todo
  and edit the migration file.


    class AddUsersToTodo < ActiveRecord::Migration
      def self.up
        add_users :todos
      end

      def self.down
        remove_users :todos
      end
    end


2. Edit environment.rb

  Add observers.

    config.active_record.observers = :leapfrog_observer

3. If it is running on development enviroment edit
   config/enviroments/development.rb

    config.cache_classes = true # false(default) -> true

4. LeapfrogObserver u/c

      observe :user # need to define observe :target_table

   I will define to YAML file asap :D

